===Phonosemantic interpretation===

[[w:Old_Chinese|Old Chinese]] [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Initials|Initial]] {{IPAchar|/*s-/}} lends semantic value '''Small/Thin/Slender'''. [[w:Old_Chinese_phonology#Vowels|Vowel]] {{IPAchar|/*-o-/}} lends semantic value '''Curvature''' or '''Curve and surround/envelop'''.
{{liushu|p}} of fingers curled about an object such as fruit in picking, plucking or pinching it. Although 爪 originally referred to picking up/at with the fingers, it eventually came to refer to the nails → claw; scratch (at).
Source: [http://www.kanjinetworks.com/eng/kanji-dictionary/online-kanji-etymology-dictionary.cfm?kanji_id=SOGx02 Howell & Morimoto]

===Etymology===
